cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use Frame Check in academic work, please cite it using the
  metadata below. The methodology paper and frame library are
  separately citeable research artifacts; see the references block
  for canonical URLs (the hosted corpus surface at
  corpus.clarethium.com is currently paused).
title: "Frame Check: a research instrument for framing and verification in documents"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Lucic
    given-names: Lovro
    website: "https://blog.clarethium.com"
repository-code: "https://github.com/lluvr/frame-check-mcp"
url: "https://github.com/lluvr/frame-check-mcp"
abstract: >-
  Frame Check is a structural framing analysis tool and public
  research program. It names which perspectives a document takes,
  which it omits, and how it positions the reader; numerical claims
  are cross-checked against authoritative sources where coverage
  exists. The methodology is deterministic and transparent: every
  claim the tool makes is computed from pattern matchers that return
  the same result on every run, with AI-assisted interpretation
  available as a separately labelled enrichment.
keywords:
  - framing analysis
  - AI verification
  - document analysis
  - structural framing
  - source network verification
  - frame vocabulary standard
license: Apache-2.0
version: "1.0.0"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.19888849"
date-released: "2026-04-28"
